      <bioghist id="ref4">
         <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
         <p>Professor of Religious Studies at Stanford University since 1978, Harvey trained at Yale Divinity School and taught at the University of Pennsylvania before coming to Stanford.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref2">
         <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
         <p>Collection includes correspondence with Rudolf Bultmann, 1960-73, Schubert Ogden, 1960-61, D. Z. Phillips, 2004, 2006, and Alvin Plantinga, 1997-98; a radio script, “The Academy Awards,” prepared by Harvey and Bob Batchelder for Religion at the News Desk broadcast over WELI in New Haven, CT, March 22, 1952; bound copy of his dissertation “Myth, Faith, and History”; and examples of his published work including reprints, journal issues, and books.</p>
      </scopecontent>
